Carnitas Tacos with Tomatillo Salsa

Carnitas:
3 tbsp lard or canola oil
3 lbs skinless, boneless pork shoulder, cut into 3" pieces
kosher salt to taste
10 garlic cloves, peeled and smashed
1 large white onion, roughly chopped
3/4 c whole milk
3/4 c oj
1/4 c lime juice
1/4 c pickled jalapeno slices
1/4 c jalapeno pickling liquid
1 tsp orange zest

In a large dutch oven, heat the lard over medium high heat. Season the pork with salt and add to the pan. Cook, stirring as needed, until golden brown, 15 min. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to a bowl. To the pan, add the garlic and onions, and cook, until lightly golden, 5 min. Return the pork to the pan with the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to a light simmer and cook, covered, until the pork is tender when pirced with a knife, 2-2 1/2 hrs. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the pork to a bowl. Add 1 c of the braising liquid to the pork, and using 2 forks, roughyl shred the pork into bite size pieces. Season with salt.

Salsa:
1 lb (8 small) tomatillos, husked and cored
4 garlic cloves
1 jalapeno, stemmed, halved, and seeded
3 tbsp lime juice
kosher salt to taste

Heat a large cast iron skillet over high heat. Add the tomatillos, garlic, and jalapeno, and cook, turning as needed, until charred, 4-5 min. Transfer to a blender to cool. Once cooled, add juice and puree until smooth. Season with salt.


Assembly/Serving:
warm corn tortillas
roughly chopped cilantro
thinly sliced radishes
diced white onion
lime wedges
